Package org.apache.qpid.protonj2.engine

Enum TransactionState

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TransactionState>
      • org.apache.qpid.protonj2.engine.TransactionState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<TransactionState>
    public enum TransactionState
extends java.lang.Enum<TransactionState>
    Indicates the current state of a given Transaction

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant Description
      DECLARE_FAILED
      A Transaction is considered failed in the TransactionManager responds with an error to the Declare action.
      DECLARED
      A Transaction is considered declared once the TransactionManager has responded in the affirmative and assigned a transaction Id.
      DECLARING
      A Transaction is considered declaring once a Declare command has been sent to the remote but before any response has been received which assigns the transaction ID.
      DISCHARGE_FAILED
      A Transaction is considered failed in the TransactionManager responds with an error to the Discharge action.
      DISCHARGED
      A Transaction is considered discharged once a Discharge has been requested and the TransactionManager has responded in the affirmative that the request has been honored.
      DISCHARGING
      A Transaction is considered to b discharging once a Discharge command has been sent to the remote but before any response has been received indicating the outcome of the attempted discharge.
      IDLE
      A Transaction is considered IDLE until the TransactionManager responds that it has been declared successfully and an transaction Id has been assigned.
